ount needs adjustment.\n\nActually, rereading the task about \"replica counts\" being changed — I should check if the `num_replicas` in zone configs were modified. The system database and ranges all show `num_replicas = 5`, which are the built-in CockroachDB defaults, but with only 3 nodes in the StatefulSet, having `num_replicas = 5` for system ranges would cause under-replication. CockroachDB does set system ranges to 5 replicas automatically, and they function fine with 3 nodes by attempting to spread replicas across available capacity.\n\nThe main changes I can identify are the reduced snapshot rebalance rate, enabled diagnostics reporting, and the lowered GC TTL on the default range. I should write a rollback script to reset those cluster settings and the zone configuration, and note the StatefulSet replica count for reference. I need to check if there are user-defined databases with custom zone configs beyond these system zones.\n\nLooking at the zones output, I only see system zones in the `crdb_internal.zones` query, so that's the complete list. Now I'm comparing the current values against CockroachDB 24.1's factory defaults—the RANGE default should have gc.ttlseconds at 90000, the system database at 86400, the lease table at 600, and the meta range at 3.\n\nThe RANGE default with gc.ttlseconds=14400 stands out as clearly user-customized since it doesn't match the factory default of 90000. I'm trying to identify which other zone configs are non-default versus built-in, but there are a lot of system tables with varying gc.ttlseconds values that I need to sort through.\n\nFor the rollback script, I should reset the explicitly customized cluster settings and use CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds=90000 to restore RANGE default to its proper factory value rather than discarding it entirely. The StatefulSet is running at 3 replicas, which I should note.\n\nNow I'm checking which zone configurations are actually non-default by comparing against what exists in a fresh CockroachDB 24.1 cluster—there are several built-in zones like RANGE default, DATABASE system, the system lease table, and various internal ranges that come standard.\n\nThe key issue is identifying which values were user-modified versus factory defaults. The most obvious anomaly is the RANGE default gc.ttlseconds set to 14400 instead of the standard 90000, which strongly suggests user customization there.\n\nFor the rollback script, I should use cluster setting resets for non-default values and zone config resets for the ones that clearly deviate from factory defaults. The challenge is that some zone configs like the DATABASE system and RANGE system settings are uncertain without knowing the exact 24.1 factory values, though others like the lease and liveness ranges match known defaults and shouldn't be touched. I'm planning the rollback script to reset those cluster settings back to their factory defaults, along with the zone configurations for the RANGE and DATABASE system objects if they've drifted from what CockroachDB expects. I should also handle the StatefulSet replica adjustments. Let me gather more specifics about what's actually non-default in the current setup before finalizing the script.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1201,"cache_read_input_tokens":30127,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1201},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe48a56f-50f3-4cfd-b4cf-0e28611d90da","uuid":"3e986b6c-1535-4f19-99cf-9ac42ddb0813","request_id":"req_011CcMRZUoJutjsTMXyb9o7y"}
